3 SECTION 4. TRANSFER - ENTITIES UNDER THE CONTROL OF THE INDUSTRIAL
4 COMMISSION TO INDUSTRIAL COMMISSION FUND - ADMINISTRATION - EXEMPTION.
5 1. The sum of $1,818,114, or so much of the sum as may be necessary, included in the
6 appropriation in subdivision 1 of section 1 of this Act, may be transferred from the
7 entities within the control of the industrial commission or entities directed to make
8 payments to the industrial commission fund for administrative services rendered by the
9 commission. Transfers must be made during the biennium beginning July 1, 2025, and
10 ending June 30, 2027, upon order of the commission. Transfers from the student loan
11 trust fund must be made to the extent permitted by sections 54-17-24 and 54-17-25.
12 2. The amount of 1,818,114 appropriated to the industrial commission in subdivision 1 of
13 section 1 of chapter 14 of the 2023 Session Laws and transferred pursuant to
14 section 8 of chapter 14 of the 2023 Session Laws is not subject to the provisions of
15 section 54-44.1-11. Any unexpended funds from this appropriation are available to the
16 industrial commission for administrative services rendered by the commission during
17 the biennium beginning July 1, 2025, and ending June 30, 2027.
18 SECTION 5. TRANSFER - BANK OF NORTH DAKOTA PROFITS TO GENERAL FUND.
19 The Bank of North Dakota shall transfer $140,000,000 from the Bank's current earnings and
20 undivided profits to the general fund during the biennium beginning July 1, 2025, and ending
21 June 30, 2027. The moneys must be transferred in the amount and at the times requested by
22 the director of the office of management and budget after consultation with the Bank president.
23 For legislative council budget status reporting purposes, the transfer under this section is
24 considered an ongoing revenue source.
