4 SECTION 7. LIGNITE RESEARCH, DEVELOPMENT, AND MARKETING PROGRAM -
5 LIGNITE MARKETING FEASIBILITY STUDY - REPORT TO THE SEVENTIETH
6 LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY.
7 1. Pursuant to the continuing appropriation under section 57-61-01.6, up to $4,500,000
8 from the lignite research fund may be used for the purpose of contracting for an
9 independent, nonmatching lignite marketing feasibility study or studies that determine
10 those focused priority areas where near-term, market-driven projects, activities, or
11 processes will generate matching private industry investment and have the most
12 potential of preserving existing lignite production and industry jobs or that will lead to
13 increased development of lignite and its products and create new lignite industry jobs
14 and economic growth for the general welfare of this state. Moneys designated under
15 this section also may be used for the purpose of contracting for nonmatching studies
16 and activities in support of advanced energy technology and other technology
17 development programs; for litigation that may be necessary to protect and promote the
18 continued development of lignite resources; for nonmatching externality studies and
19 activities in externality proceedings; or other marketing, environmental, or transmission
20 activities that assist with marketing of lignite-based electricity and lignite-based
21 byproducts. Moneys needed for the purposes stated in this section are available to the
22 industrial commission for funding projects, processes, or activities under the lignite
23 research, development, and marketing program.
24 2. The industrial commission shall report to the appropriations committees of the
25 seventieth legislative assembly on the amounts spent pursuant to this section.
